summary: At the Inn at the Crossroads
body:
At the Inn at the Crossroads

Polliver: “Listen, Sandor, I’m in the middle of something more important than whatever… THIS is. So if you just want to run along and bring back someone substantial, say, I don’t know… Ser Gregor? That’d be great.”

Sandor “The Hound” Clegane: (sighs and proceeds to draw his sword)

Polliver: (sarcastically) “Oh, what’s wrong, Hound? Did I touch a nerve?”

Arya Stark: “You pulled the Mountain lever.”

Polliver: “Excuse me, but what-”

(Sandor proceeds to swing his sword down on Polliver)

Sandor “The Hound” Clegane: “Ya shouldn’t -a did that.”
